    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect parameter passing in dump_dlsch2() function calls\n\n### Summary\nThe `dump_dlsch2()` function in the LTE PHY layer had inconsistent calling conventions across multiple simulation files. Some calls were missing required parameters, while others passed values instead of pointers, causing undefined behavior when the function was invoked for debugging purposes.\n\nThe issue was particularly evident when running TM7 simulations where the function would access invalid memory locations due to missing HARQ process ID parameters.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/dlsim_tm7.c`: Added missing `harq_pid` parameter to two `dump_dlsch2()` calls\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/syncsim.c`: Added missing `subframe` and `harq_pid` parameters to `dump_dlsch2()` call\n- `openair1/SIMULATION/LTE_PHY/dlsim_tm4.c`: Fixed parameter passing to use address-of operator for `coded_bits_per_codeword`\n\nWhen running simulations with debug output enabled, these incorrect calls would previously cause segmentation faults or produce garbled debug output files. The fix ensures all calls match the declared function signature in the header files.\n"
}